### Create an order
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "customer_email": "alice@example.com",
    "customer_name": "Alice",
    "amount_cents": 14999,
    "currency": "usd"
}

### Get an order by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/orders/5

### Create payment via stripe-integration for an order
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders/5/pay

### Create another order
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "customer_email": "bob@example.com",
    "customer_name": "Bob",
    "amount_cents": 3950
}

### Cancel an order
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders/2/cancel

### Invalid create (should fail with 400)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "customer_email": "",
    "amount_cents": 0
}

### Get non-existent order (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/orders/99999

### Internal callback sync (payment succeeded)
POST http://localhost:8080/internal/payments/stripe-webhook
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "order_id": "1",
    "payment_intent_id": "pi_test_123",
    "event_type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
    "status": "succeeded"
}

### Internal callback sync (event not handled)
POST http://localhost:8080/internal/payments/stripe-webhook
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "order_id": "1",
    "payment_intent_id": "pi_test_123",
    "event_type": "payment_intent.processing",
    "status": "processing"
}
